The root cause is that **ASP.NET Core 10's `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` upgrades from OpenAPI.NET v1.x to v2.x**, which has several breaking changes. Here's every issue in your code and how to fix it:

---

### 1. `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace removed
All `OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, etc. types are gone. Use `System.Text.Json.Nodes` instead.

```csharp
// OLD
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// NEW — JsonNode has implicit conversions from primitives
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = "1.0";
```

---

### 2. `schema.Nullable` property removed
OpenAPI 3.1 (which v2 targets) uses JSON Schema type arrays instead of a separate `nullable` keyword. `Type` is now a `JsonSchemaType` flags enum.

```csharp
// OLD
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// NEW — clear the Null flag
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

---

### 3. `Reference` property removed from model base types
v2 uses dedicated reference-proxy types instead of setting `.Reference` on the model.

```csharp
// OLD
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
{
    Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
};

// NEW — use the reference type directly
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
```

---

### 4. Collections are no longer auto-initialized
`Parameters`, `Responses`, `Security`, `Properties`, `Required`, etc. can all be `null` on a freshly-created object. Guard with `??=` or `?.`.

```csharp
// OLD
operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", ...);

// NEW
operation.Responses ??= new Dictionary<string, OpenApiResponse>();
operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });
```

---

### Full corrected code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;      // replaces Microsoft.OpenApi.Any
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters?.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = "1.0";   // JsonNode implicit conversion
    }

    operation.Responses ??= new Dictionary<string, OpenApiResponse>();
    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    // Use the reference-proxy type instead of setting .Reference
    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;  // replaces Nullable = false
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

**Summary of what moved where:**

| v1 (OpenAPI.NET 1.x)                | v2 (OpenAPI.NET 2.x)                              |
|--------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any`        | `using System.Text.Json.Nodes`                     |
| `new OpenApiString("1.0")`           | `"1.0"` (implicit `JsonNode`)                      |
| `schema.Nullable = true/false`       | `schema.Type \|= / &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null`        |
| `new OpenApiReference { Type, Id }`  | `new OpenApi<Model>Reference("id")`                |
| Collections always initialized       | Collections start `null` — guard with `??=` or `?.`|
